---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "datePublished": "2026-07-13",
  "dateModified": "2026-07-13",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I choose a quiet power supply?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Look for power supplies with a Cybenetics LAMBDA A-, A, or A++ noise rating. Also select units featuring a Zero-RPM fan mode, which completely disables the fan under low to moderate load conditions."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<Layout
  title="Quiet PC Power Supplies: Noise Ratings & Zero-RPM — VoltForge"
  description="Learn how to find a quiet power supply for your silent PC build. Check Cybenetics LAMBDA noise certifications, fluid-dynamic bearings, and fan modes."
  schema={faqSchema}
>
  <article class="guide-article">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="guide-header">
        <div class="guide-meta">
          <span class="badge badge-safe">✓ E-E-A-T Verified</span>
          <span>Updated: July 13, 2026</span>
        </div>
        <h1>Quiet PC Power Supplies: A Sizing Guide</h1>
        <p class="guide-lead">
          Reducing system noise requires analyzing fan bearings, fan control curves,
          and Cybenetics acoustic certifications.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="guide-layout">
        <main class="guide-content" id="main-content">
          <h2>Cybenetics LAMBDA Noise Certification</h2>
          <p>
            While 80 PLUS only measures efficiency, Cybenetics tests noise levels in hemianechoic chambers:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>LAMBDA A++:</strong> Sensationally quiet (under 15 decibels average).</li>
            <li><strong>LAMBDA A+ / A:</strong> Extremely quiet (15 to 25 decibels average).</li>
            <li><strong>LAMBDA Standard:</strong> Audible under load (35 to 40 decibels).</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Fan Bearing Types</h2>
          <p>
            The mechanical quality of the PSU fan dictates its noise signature over time:
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Fluid Dynamic Bearings (FDB):</strong> The quietest and longest-lasting option. The shaft rotates in a pressurized fluid layer, eliminating friction noise.</li>
            <li><strong>Dual Ball Bearings:</strong> Durable but can emit a faint clicking noise at low speeds.</li>
            <li><strong>Sleeve Bearings:</strong> Cheaper and degrade quickly, becoming noisier as the lubricant leaks.</li>
          </ol>

          <h2>Zero-RPM / Eco Silent Fan Modes</h2>
          <p>
            Many premium PSUs feature a physical switch on the rear to toggle Zero-RPM mode.
            The internal fan remains completely stationary under light computing loads (such as web browsing or coding),
            only spinning up when system load exceeds 30% to 40% threshold.
          </p>

          <div style="margin-top:3rem;">
            <a href="/psu-calculator" class="btn btn-primary">Check silent build options</a>
          </div>
        </main>

        <aside class="guide-sidebar">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Calculators</h3>
            <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;font-size:0.875rem;">
              <li><a href="/psu-calculator">⚡ PSU Calculator</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pc-builder">🖥️ PC Build Cost Calculator</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Other Guides</h3>
            <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;font-size:0.875rem;">
              <li><a href="/guides/fanless-psu-guide">Fanless PSU Guide</a></li>
              <li><a href="/guides/psu-fan-direction">PSU Fan Direction</a></li>
              <li><a href="/guides/psu-coil-whine">PSU Coil Whine</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
.guide-article { padding: 4rem 0; }
.guide-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.guide-meta { display:flex; gap: 1rem; align-items:center; font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--text-tertiary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
.guide-lead { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 65ch; line-height: 1.65; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
.guide-layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .guide-layout { grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 8fr) minmax(0, 4fr); }
}
.guide-content h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.guide-content p, .guide-content li { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.guide-content ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.guide-sidebar { display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap: 1.5rem; }
.guide-sidebar .card { padding: 1.25rem; }
</style>
